    <measure>Incidence of cardiac failure and the impact of cardiac problems on morbidity</measure>
    <time_frame>6 months</time_frame>
    <safety_issue>No</safety_issue>
    <description>The aims of the study are:
to document the incidence of myocardial dysfunction
to find the predictive factors of myocardial dysfunction as determined by the severity aneurysmal bleeding (Hunt and Hess-grading, Glasgow coma score, Fisher scale) and demographic factors
to find  predictive factors for myocardial dysfunction as determined by laboratory findings, electrocardiography, and echocardiography
to describe heart rate variability
to assess the impact of all cardiac problems on morbidity</description>
  </primary_outcome>
